<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: [REQUEST] Animated graphic equalizer start button?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5160&amp;p=22325#p22325"><![CDATA[
Hey Zoni, pretty much anybody could do it, even you.<br /><br />Start out simple, by using the middle image.<br />It's size is already 50 pixels by 50 pixels.<br />Lets say you go for qty 11 frames, to make it easy.<br />Do the math: Width=50 pixels.<br />Height 50x11=550+1(the pixel code line at the very top)=551<br />So just open a photo program, make a blank new image with 50x551 size. <br />Copy and paste the bar gragh image 11 times, stacking them up vertically, <br />leaving the top of new image with the blank 1 pixel line. Then merge it all together.<br />To make it easy, copy someone elses top coded pixel line, that has 11 frames, <br />and paste it starting at the very top left. Merge. <br />I'm sure if you borrow the top line from Situla's great rotating cube file, he or she won't mind. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />Now the fun begins. Just pick black color, and randomly black out the colors on each frame.<br />Save as .png or .bmp file. Even 24 bit works in this case, so any photo program can make it.<br />Load it in CSM with size at 41, done. <br /><br />If you managed to accomplish that, then you can read more into the guide, <br />and make a better longer running one, as there is no looping feature. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Thu Sep 17, 2015 11:55 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
